      "span_text": "The eigenvector and semidefinite programming methods for solving an instance of the synchronization problem were originally introduced by Singer in in the context of angular synchronization, where one is asked to estimate n unknown angles θ 1,., θ n ∈ [0, 2π) given m noisy measurements δ ij of their offsets θ i − θ j mod 2π."
